column12:
The UES Self-Discovery Inventory (the “UES-SDI”) provided to you has been prepared by USA-UES. If you complete the UES-SDI, we treat your responses and your results as confidential information. Your personal information will not be shared with or sold to third parties.
 
 Please note that the accuracy of your survey results will depend on how precisely and honestly you answer the questions.Please enter your name below, which will indicate that you voluntarily agree to participate in it.
column13:
使用条款 “优易思自我发现问卷” （以下统称为“该问卷”）由美国-优易思公司为您提供，并归美国-优易思公司版权所有。我们将对您在该问卷中提供的结果和信息进行严格保密，并承诺杜绝将您的个人信息分享或转卖给第三方个人及机构。
调查结果的准确与否将取决于您答题的准确性与诚实度。若您理解并同意本条款，请在空白处填写您的姓名全拼。签名将作为您自愿参与该问卷并遵守本条款所有内容的证明依据。

column12: In your perception, what would a life and school environment of studying abroad in the US look like? Tell us how much do you agree or disagree with each of these statements.
column13: 在你看来，在美国留学的生活和学校环境会是什么样子？告诉我们您对这些陈述有多少不同意或同意。

column12: Studying in China is much harder than studying abroad.
column13: 在中国读书比在国外读书难多了。

column12: It is easier to apply to U.S. colleges.
column13: 美国的大学更容易申请。

column12: It is easy to do well in the U.S. college.
column13: 在美国学习更轻松。

column12: Life is free in U.S., so I can do whatever I want.
column13: 在美国生活没有什么约束，想做什么就做什么。

column12: Values are the general expression of what is most important to you. Here is a set of cultural values. Please indicate the degree to which you agree or disagree. Remember, there is no right or wrong answer.
column13: 人们最在意的事情往往可以从价值观来体现。下列是一些关于文化的价值观。请表明你对它们不同意或同意的程度。没有正确或错误的答案，所以请真实的表达自己。

column12: Valuing education
column13: 重视教育

column12: Accumulating wealth
column13: 累积财富

column12: Protecting your "face"
column13: 要面子

column12: Ordering relationships by status and observing this order
column13: 尊卑有序

column12: Having respects for traditions
column13: 尊重传统习俗

column12: Supporting your parents financially
column13: 赡养父母

column12: Having respects for the elderly
column13: 尊敬长辈

column12: Obeying parents and superiors
column13: 服从父母和上级

column12: Having contentedness with one's position in life
column13: 安分守己

column12: Having few desires
column13: 无欲无求

column12: Being non-competitive
column13: 不爱竞争

column12: People have different opinions regarding the relationship between hard work and talent. Please indicate how much you agree or disagree with the following statements.
column13: 人们对目前无法实现的目标抱有不同的态度：有些人认为，只要努力，他们就可以实现他们原本无法实现的目标；有些人认为很多事情在很大程度上已经注定。你有什么看法？

column12: You can learn new things, but you cannot really change your basic level of intelligence.
column13: 人可以学习新的知识，但是无法改变基本智力水平。

column12: I like my work best when I can do it really well without too much trouble.
column13: 我只喜欢做简单的事情，因为我不想花太多功夫。

column12: I like my work best when I can do it perfectly without any mistakes.
column13: 我只喜欢做简单的事情，因为我全能做对。

column12: To tell the truth, when I work hard, it makes me feel as though I'm not very smart.
column13: 当我花很多时间做一件事情的时候，我会感觉自己不够聪明。

column12: No matter how much intelligence you have, you can always change it a good deal.
column13: 智力水平在一定程度上受后天因素的影响。

column12: I like my work best when it makes me think hard.
column13: 我喜欢做能挑战我思维的事情。

column12: I like work that I'll learn from even if I make a lot of mistakes.
column13: 我不介意做困难的事情， 因为即使犯了错也能从中学到东西。

column12: When something is hard, it just makes me want to work more on it, not less
column13: 当一件事情很难的时候，它会让我想要下更多的功夫。

column12: Here is a set of learning strategies. Please tell us how often you apply these strategies to your own study. Again, be as accurate as possible.
column13: 以下是一些学习方法，请评价你有多不同意或同意这些陈述。

column12: I usually try to think about the bigger picture during a discussion to ensure that the discussion does not deviate from the theme.
column13: 我会在讨论中尝试顾全大局把握大方向，确保讨论不会偏离主题。

column12: I use more than one source to find out information for myself.
column13: 我利用不同渠道来查找信息。

column12: I am often on the lookout for new ideas.
column13: 我会寻找一些新思路、尝试一些新方法。

column12: I sometimes find a good argument that challenges some of my firmly held beliefs.
column13: 我会肯定一些与我不同但是很中肯的观点。

column12: It's important to understand other people's viewpoints on an issue.
column13: 我认为了解其他人对某个问题的观点很重要。

column12: It is important to justify the choices I make.
column13: 我认为仔细验证我的决定是否正确是一件很重要的事

column12: I often reevaluate my experiences so that I can learn from them.
column13: 我会反思自己的经历并从中学习。

column12: I usually check the credibility of the source of information before making judgements.
column13: 我会先检查信息来源的可信度，再做出判断。

column12: I usually think about the wider implications of a decision before taking action.
column13: 我做决定之前会考虑该决定的影响。

column12: I often think about my actions and whether I could improve them.
column13: 我会反思自己的行为并改进。

column12: You are halfway through! In this section, we are interested in learning about your studying habits. Please rate how often you have the following behaviors.  Please try to be as accurate as possible.
column13:
评估已经进行一半！
在本节中，我们希望了解你的学习习惯。请你估计一下你有下列行为的频率。请尽量准确作答。

column12: I know when I understand something.
column13: 我能清晰的知道自己是否理解某个概念，不会模棱两可。

column12: I ask myself how well I am doing while I am learning something new.
column13: 学习新知识时，我会反思自己对新知识掌握的程度。

column12: I really pay attention to important information.
column13: 对于关键的信息，我会更加专心地去听。

column12: I learn more when I am interested in the topic.
column13: 当我对某个话题感兴趣时，我会学到更多东西。

column12: I use my learning strengths to make up for my weaknesses.
column13: 在学习一门课时，我能认清自己的强项并扬长避短。

column12: I use different learning strategies depending on the task.
column13: 根据不同的内容，我会使用不同的学习技巧。

column12: I occasionally check to make sure I’ll get my work done on time.
column13: 我时不时地检查进度以确保能按时完成作业。

column12: I sometimes use learning strategies without thinking.
column13: 我会习惯性地使用一些学习技巧。

column12: I ask myself if there was an easier way to do things after I finish a task.
column13: 完成任务后， 我会反思自己的做事方法并设法在下次提高。

column12: I decide what I need to get done before I start a task.
column13: 在开始一项工作之前，我会提前想好需要做什么。

column12: I can make myself learn when I need to.
column13: 当需要学习时，我能自觉学习。

column12: I try to use ways of studying that have worked for me before.
column13: 我会尽可能用以前用过的有效的学习方法。

column12: I know what the teacher expects me to learn.
column13: 我能抓到老师讲课的重点。

column12: I learn best when I already know something about the topic.
column13: 当我对某个话题有一定了解的时候，我学得很快。

column12: I draw pictures or diagrams to help me understand while learning.
column13: 在学习的时候，我会通过画图或列表来帮助自己理解。

column12: When I am done with my schoolwork, I ask myself what I have learned.
column13: 当我完成功课时，我会回想学到了什么。

column12: I think of several ways to solve a problem and then choose the best.
column13: 我会想好几种解决问题的方法，然后选择最好的。

column12: I think about what I need to learn before I start working.
column13: 在开始学习之前，我会想想我应该掌握到什么程度。

column12: Here is a set of learning strategies. Please tell us how often you apply these strategies to your own study. Again, be as accurate as possible.
column13: 以下是一些学习方法，请评价你有多不同意或同意这些陈述。

column12: I review my lecture notes regularly, even when a test is not imminent.
column13: 我会定期复习课堂笔记，而不是只在考试前复习。

column12: I find it hard to stick to a study schedule.
column13: 我发现我很难坚持一个固定的学习时间表。

column12: I set and keep priorities.
column13: 我会把事情按重要性排序，并先做最重要的。

column12: I make good use of time.
column13: 我能充分利用时间。

column12: I continue to carry out unproductive routines or activities.
column13: 我会把时间浪费在一些无用的日常活动上。

column12: I am still working on a major assignment the night before it is due.
column13: 我会把作业拖到最后一刻才写。

column12: I make sure that I keep up with the weekly readings and assignments for this course.
column13: 我会将课程材料整理总结成大纲，从而帮助我理清思路。

column12: I make a list of the things I have to do each week.
column13: 我会制作简单的图表来帮助我整理课程材料。

column12: I plan each day before I start it.
column13: 学习时，我会通读课本和笔记，并画出重点。

column12: I write a set of goals for myself regularly.
column13: 我确保完成老师布置的阅读和作业。

column12: When I study the readings for a course, I outline the material to help me organize my thoughts.
column13: 我会把每周要做的事情列一个清单。

column12: I make simple charts, diagrams, or tables to help me organize course material.
column13: 我会在每天开始学习之前制定计划。

column12: When I study for this course, I go through the readings and my class notes and try to find the most important ideas.
column13: 我会经常为自己设立一些目标。

column12: In the past two weeks, how often do you experience the following feeling?
column13: 在过去的两周里，您是否有下列感觉？如果有，有多频繁？

column12: Little interest or pleasure in doing things
column13: 做事情没有什么兴趣或乐趣。

column12: If any of these happened to you, how much impact do they have in your life or study?
column13: 如果以上情景在您的身上发生，这些问题对您的学习和与其他人相处有多大影响？

column12: Feeling down, depressed, or hopeless
column13: 感觉很沮丧，绝望，无助。

column12: Trouble falling or staying asleep, or sleeping too much
column13: 失眠或睡不好，或睡得太多。

column12: Feeling tired or having little energy
column13: 感到疲劳或精力不足。

column12: Poor appetite or overeating
column13: 食欲不振或暴饮暴食。

column12: Feeling bad about yourself—or that you are a failure or have let yourself or your family down
column13: 觉得自己很糟糕，感觉自己是个失败者，让家人失望。

column12: Trouble concentrating on things, such as reading the newspaper or watching television
column13: 难以集中注意力，例如看报纸或看电视。

column12: Moving or speaking so slowly that other people could have noticed. Or the opposite—being so restless that you have been moving around a lot more than usual
column13: 行动或说话很缓慢，以至于其他人可能已经注意到了。或者相反，您的情绪很焦躁，以至于您比平常更加活跃。

column12: Thoughts that you would be better off dead, or of hurting yourself in some way
column13: 想到过死了会更好，或者以某种方式来伤害自己。

column12: Our actions, desires, and needs are all supported by various reasons. These reasons guide our behavior and are what cause a person to want to repeat it. We know studying can be hard, and we are very interested in knowing your reasons for studying.
column13: 人们的行动，愿望和需求都有各种原因。这些原因引导着人们的行为，鼓励着他们前进。我们理解学习不是一件容易的事情，所以我们很想了解你坚持学习的原因。

column12: Because eventually it will enable me to enter the job market in a field that I like
column13: 因为学习能帮我进入我喜欢领域的就业市场。

column12: Because this will help me make a better choice regarding my career orientation
column13: 因为学习将帮助我在职业定位方面做出更好的选择。

column12: To prove to myself that I am capable of getting good grades
column13: 因为可以向自己证明自己有能力取得好成绩。

column12: Because of the fact that when I succeed in school I feel important
column13: 因为取得好成绩时我会在学校被重视。

column12: Other accomplishments______
Because I need a college degree to find a high-paying job later on
column13: 因为我需要大学学历来找高薪的工作。

column12: In order to obtain a more prestigious job later on
column13: 为了以后获得更有社会地位的工作。

column12: Because I experience pleasure and satisfaction while learning new things
column13: 因为我在学习新事物同时感受到快乐和满足。

column12: For the pleasure that I experience in broadening my knowledge about subjects which appeal to me
column13: 在我感兴趣的领域开阔视野让我感到快乐。

column12: For the pleasure I experience while surpassing myself in my studies
column13: 因为在学习中超越自我的快乐。

column12: For the satisfaction I feel when I am in the process of accomplishing difficult academic activities
column13: 因为完成困难的学术活动时我能获得满足感。

column12: For the intense feelings I experience when I am communicating my own ideas to others
column13: 因为我很享受和别人交流自己的想法。

column12: For the pleasure that I experience when I read interesting material
column13: 因为阅读我有兴趣的材料使我感到快乐。

column12: Honestly, I don’t know; I really feel that I am wasting my time in school
column13: 老实说，我不知道;我真的觉得我在学校浪费时间。

column12:
We are very interested in knowing more about who you are! Here are a number of adjectives that may or may not describe you. Indicate the extent to which you agree or disagree with that statement.

column12: Different people have different ways of dealing with issues. Imagine you are working on a project or goal, how well would the following statements describe you? Try to be as honest as possible.
column13: 不同的人有不同的方法来处理事情。想象一下，如果你面对这些情况或在追求某些目标的过程中，以下的陈述是否符合你？请尽量将自己代入情景，并准确做答。

column12: New ideas and projects sometimes distract me from previous ones.
column13: 有时新的想法或事情会使我分心。

column12: My interests change from year to year.
column13: 我的兴趣会经常变化。

column12: I have overcome setbacks to conquer an important challenge.
column13: 我克服过挫折，战胜过挑战。

column12: Setbacks don’t discourage me.
column13: 挫折不会使我气馁。

column12: I have been obsessed with a certain idea or project for a short time but later lost interest.
column13: 我对事情经常三分钟热度。

column12: I am a hard worker.
column13: 我工作很努力。

column12: I often set a goal but later choose to pursue a different one.
column13: 我会经常改变我追求的目标。

column12: I have difficulty maintaining my focus on projects that take more than a few months to complete.
column13: 如果一个项目需要几个月以上的时间完成，我会很难专注。

column12: I finish whatever I begin.
column13: 只要我开始了，无论如何我也要完成它。

column12: I am diligent.
column13: 我很勤奋。

column12: I have achieved a goal that took years of work.
column13: 我曾经努力并实现了长期（长于一年）的目标。

column12: Adapt to change
column13: 我能适应变化

column12: Handle unpleasant feelings
column13: 我可以处理不愉快的情绪。

column12: Deal with whatever comes
column13: 我能克服一切困难

column12: Try to see humorous side of problems
column13: 我能尝试看到问题积极的一面

column12: Cope with stress because I believe it can strengthen me
column13: 我相信承受压力之后我会变强。

column12: Bounce back after illness or hardship
column13: 我能在受到重大打击之后重整旗鼓。

column12: Achieve goals despite obstacles
column13: 尽管遇到障碍，我仍可实现目标。

column12: Stay focused under pressure
column13: 我能在压力下保持专注。

column12: Not be easily discouraged by failure
column13: 我不容易因失败而气馁。

column12: Think of self as strong person
column13: 我认为自己是个坚强的人。

column12: I don't think students and teachers need much communication under the class
column13: 我觉得学生和老师课下不需要有太多交流。

column12: I am a very independent learner.
column13: 我是一个很自觉的学生。

column12: Class size is not important to me.
column13: 班级规模的大小对我来说不重要。

column12: I'm looking for a school with extensive research facilities.
column13: 我希望在一所有完善的研究设施的学校读书。

column12: I have a major in mind already.
column13: 我有想读的专业。

column12: I like attending big sporting events.
column13: 我喜欢参加大型体育赛事。

column12: I love meeting new people.
column13: 我喜欢结识新朋友。

column12: I enjoy being exposed to unfamiliar situations and perspectives and having a wide variety of social experiences in general.
column13: 我喜欢接触不同的人群和观点，从而积累广泛的社会经验。
